long paddock
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:The grassed borders of a public road used by farmers for grazing stock; the grass or grazing along roadsides; also called long acre.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
